

## Usage

- Access the API at `http://localhost:3000`
- Use routes like `/customers`, `/accounts`, and `/transactions` to interact with the data.

## Routes

### GET /

- Description: Displays a welcome message.
- Example: `GET /`

### GET /customers

- Description: Retrieves a list of customers.
- Example: `GET /customers`

### GET /accounts

- Description: Retrieves a list of accounts.
- Example: `GET /accounts`

### GET /transactions

- Description: Retrieves a list of transactions.
- Example: `GET /transactions`

### GET /customers/:id

- Description: Retrieves a single customer by ID.
- Example: `GET /customers/60c8dd1e3831320015e48b24`

### DELETE /:id

- Description: Deletes a single customer by ID.
- Example: `DELETE /customers/60c8dd1e3831320015e48b24`

### POST /

- Description: Creates a new customer.
- Example: `POST /`

### PATCH /customers/:id

- Description: Updates a customer by ID.
- Example: `PATCH /customers/60c8dd1e3831320015e48b24`

